### Frontend Property API Tests
### Base URL
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api
@token = YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 1. Get All Properties
GET {{baseUrl}}/properties
Content-Type: application/json

### 2. Get Properties with Filters
GET {{baseUrl}}/properties?city=New York&minPrice=100&maxPrice=500
Content-Type: application/json

### 3. Search Properties
GET {{baseUrl}}/properties?search=luxury
Content-Type: application/json

### 4. Get Property by ID
@propertyId = YOUR_PROPERTY_ID_HERE
GET {{baseUrl}}/properties/{{propertyId}}
Content-Type: application/json

### 5. Create Property (Host Only)
# First, register and login as a host to get a token
POST {{baseUrl}}/properties
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Luxury Beach House",
  "description": "Beautiful beachfront property with stunning ocean views",
  "pricePerNight": 350,
  "cleaningFee": 75,
  "bedrooms": 3,
  "bathrooms": 2,
  "maxGuests": 6,
  "address": "456 Ocean Drive",
  "city": "Miami",
  "country": "USA",
  "latitude": 25.7617,
  "longitude": -80.1918,
  "amenities": ["WiFi", "Pool", "Beach Access", "Kitchen", "Parking"],
  "propertyType": "House",
  "images": [
    "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1499793983690-e29da59ef1c2",
    "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1502672260066-6bc05c107db4"
  ]
}

### 6. Update Property (Owner Only)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/properties/{{propertyId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Updated Luxury Beach House",
  "pricePerNight": 400
}

### 7. Delete Property (Owner Only)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/properties/{{propertyId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 8. Get My Listings (Host Only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/properties/my-listings
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

### ===== AUTHENTICATION FLOW =====

### Register as Host
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "host-test@example.com",
  "password": "HostPass123",
  "firstName": "Test",
  "lastName": "Host",
  "isHost": true
}

### Login as Host
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "host-test@example.com",
  "password": "HostPass123"
}

### Get Current User
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json
